The course uses practical exercises to give an overview of the language structure within the level of B2 / C1 in the Estonian language. Basic vocabulary is repeatedly used. Focus is on form preferences that are morphological similar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of the structure of the Estonian language within the B2  language level; to cover the grammatical categories required on the B2 language level;  to cover the formation and specifics of usage of words that are prone to be use incorrectly.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who passed the subject: * knows basic language grammar on the B2 language level; * knows basic models of basic grammatical categories and can use them in speech and writing; * can utilize the analogy principle when using (conjugating and inflecting) words; * can apply the most important spelling and punctuation rules in Estonian language.
